<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-04-16T22:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-04-16T22:36:00-05:00" n="1065" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1065">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/3616.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Ambassador</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams.—Paraphrases.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-04-16T21:00:00-06:36">
                                    <hi rend="italic">April 16, 1912—9 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>At his own request I sent to the Minister for Foreign Affairs my note
                            based on Department’s April 14, 3 p.m., late in the evening, as the
                            Minister wished to avoid public expression. Comments on the alleged
                            undiplomatic character of the note and its publication appear in the
                            press, with report that the Minister will not accept the conclusions of
                            the note. The Cabinet is now considering the Government’s reply.</p>
                        <p>The arms and ammunition for the American colony are now in the hands of
                            the committee.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>